1.00	Lydia_Reed	Lydia Reed	Lydia Reed (born August 23, 1944, at Mitchel Field on Long Island, New York) is an American former child actress best known for her role as Tallahassee "Hassie" McCoy from 1957 to 1963 in 145 episodes of the ABC situation comedy The Real McCoys, starring Walter Brennan in the title role of Grandpa Amos McCoy. Irving Pincus was the creator, and Hy Averback the first principal director.	
